                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13616734" author="mgrover" created="Thu, 28 Mar 2013 22:22:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Had an extra whitespace in the previous patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13616781" author="mgrover" created="Thu, 28 Mar 2013 23:11:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI: The patch applies cleanly on both &lt;tt&gt;trunk&lt;/tt&gt; as well as &lt;tt&gt;branch-0.11&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13616845" author="cheolsoo" created="Thu, 28 Mar 2013 23:49:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. I ran into this in the past by myself. The minus sign makes packaging fail on certain OSes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13616862" author="cheolsoo" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2013 00:04:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk. I didn&apos;t commit to 0.11.1 because the RC is already on vote, and I don&apos;t think we want to respin another RC for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13617494" author="mgrover" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2013 16:42:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cheolsoo&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cheolsoo&quot;&gt;Cheolsoo Park&lt;/a&gt; It&apos;s ok to commit to just trunk if the vote is going on. And, thanks for committing this!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13617712" author="rvs" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2013 20:53:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cheolsoo, it would be &lt;b&gt;extremely&lt;/b&gt; appreciated if this can be made part of 0.11.1 since then it would make Bigtop use one less workaround. Any chance this could happen?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13617752" author="mgrover" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2013 21:37:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, that would be really nice. In general, Apache Bigtop can help out with testing of Pig release candidates so we can find issues like this before a release goes out. In particular, I would be happy to help out with integration testing of the new release candidate against Hadoop 2 via Apache Bigtop, if it does get released.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13617834" author="cheolsoo" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2013 22:48:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rvs&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rvs&quot;&gt;Roman Shaposhnik&lt;/a&gt;, the vote is passed now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://search-hadoop.com/m/p847u1NntBe/%255BVOTE%255D+Release+Pig+0.11.1+%2528candidate+0%2529&amp;amp;subj=+VOTE+Release+Pig+0+11+1+candidate+0+&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://search-hadoop.com/m/p847u1NntBe/%255BVOTE%255D+Release+Pig+0.11.1+%2528candidate+0%2529&amp;amp;subj=+VOTE+Release+Pig+0+11+1+candidate+0+&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please express your concern to the pig-dev mailing list? I believe that Bill is going to proceed the release otherwise. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13617843" author="mgrover" created="Fri, 29 Mar 2013 23:01:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, let me do that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13619377" author="mgrover" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2013 01:39:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;If someone runs into this same issue, please try doing the following before the build:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
export LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The credit for the above workaround goes to Bruno Mah&#233;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13626776" author="cheolsoo" created="Tue, 9 Apr 2013 17:28:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed the patch to 0.11.2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13626780" author="rvs" created="Tue, 9 Apr 2013 17:29:22 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks a million!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
